ls â€“ list directory contents
ls [-FGRSTahlort] [--color=when] [file ...]

-F # suffix items with / in output if item is DIR
-G # colorizes output (DIRs are blue) or use --color
-R # recursively list subdirectories encountered
-S # sort by size (largest file first)
-T # display complete time information for the file [in -l] 
-a # show all (include hidden files)
-h # human-readable file size [in -l]
-l # list files in long format
-o # omit group id
-r # reverse the order of the sort
-t # sort by descending time modified (most recently modified first)

